<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1403.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. Jackson’s No. 2061, of the 5th
                            instant, has been received, and his refusal to issue to Gustav Frank
                            Eichborn a passport, under the circumstances set forth in the dispatch,
                            has the Department’s approval.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>